<html><head><title>The Economist: Summaries by e-mail</title></head>
<!-- Changed by: Azeem Azhar, 20-Aug-1996 -->
<!-- Approved by: John Peet, 20-Aug-1996-->
<body bgcolor=#F5FFE1>
<ul>
<br>

<img src="http://www.economist.com/econlogosmall.gif" width=78 height=39  border=0 alt="The Economist">


<head>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h1><font size=5>Receive Politics and Business This Week by e-mail</font></h1>
You can now receive our Business and Politics This Week summaries by e-mail. This is a free service. To get it, you simply need to fill out your details on one of the <a href=#form>forms below</a>. Each summary is sent out at around 7.00pm London time every Thursday. They should arrive within twelve hours.<P>
<H3>Some hints</H3>

<uL>
<li>Keep the joining messages that you receive as these will contain instructions on how to stop receiving either summary.
<li>Check your e-mail address carefully; if you get it wrong, your subscription request will fail. If you do not receive a welcome message and a transaction report then something has gone wrong: in most cases, the problem will be a mistyped e-mail address.
</uL>
<H3>Notes for America Online users</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Your Internet e-mail address is your AOL user name followed by @aol.com <BR>
eg, If your user name is abcdefg, your e-mail address is abcdefg@aol.com
</ul>
<H3>Notes for CompuServe users</H3>
<UL>
<LI>Your Internet e-mail address is your CompuServe user id, with the middle comma replaced by a full stop, followed by @compuserve.com<BR>
eg, If your user id is 70000,1000, your e-mail address is 70000.1000@compuserve.com
</ul>

<hr>
<a name=form><h2>Politics This Week</h2>
To receive a summary of the world's main political events, 
please enter your e-mail address here and press the join button. <font size=2>Your e-mail address must have an @ sign in it.</font> 
<form action="http://www.net-shopper.co.uk/cgi-bin/mailto.exe" method="post">
<input type=hidden name="sendto" value="newscaster@postbox.co.uk">
<input type=hidden name="resulturl" value="http://www.economist.com/mailing/donepol.html">
<input type=hidden name="server" value="mail.net-shopper.co.uk">
<input type=hidden name="action" value="join">
<input type=hidden name="listname" value="economist-politics">
<input type=hidden name="email_required" value="Please enter your email address.">
<p>E-mail address: <input type=text size=30 maxlength=256 name="email"> <input type=submit value="Join Economist-politics"> </p>
</form>
<p>You will receive two e-mail messages as a response - a transaction report and a welcome 
message. You can safely discard the transaction report.</p>

<STRONG>Leaving the list</STRONG><BR>
If you want to stop receiving Politics This Week, type your e-mail address in the box below and press the leave button.
<form action="http://www.net-shopper.co.uk/cgi-bin/mailto.exe" method="post">
<input type=hidden name="sendto" value="newscaster@postbox.co.uk">
<input type=hidden name="resulturl" value="http://www.economist.com/mailing/done.html">
<input type=hidden name="server" value="mail.net-shopper.co.uk">
<input type=hidden name="action" value="leave">
<input type=hidden name="listname" value="economist-politics">
