<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Stephen Budiansky is a senior writer at U.S News &amp; World Report, where he
writes about foreign affairs, national security and global environmental issues.
He was previously Washington editor of the journal Nature, and has written
about science and nature for many publications, including The Economist, The
Atlantic, Science and The New York Times. He holds an M.S. degree from
Harvard University in applied mathematics, and is the author of The Covenant
of the Wild: Why Animals Chose Domestication (shortlisted for the 1995
Rhone-Poulenc prize for Science Books). Stephen Budiansky lives on a small
farm in Virginia with his wife and two children.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?832374000,rev">Search</a>
