<h2>U<font size=-1>NCOMMON</font> G<font size=-1>ROUND</font>.<br></h2>
<p> Edited by William Cronon. <br>
<i>Norton; 560 pages; $29.95 and &#163;24</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="6jb155.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

WILLIAM CRONON is Frederick Jackson Turner Professor of History,
Geography, and Environmental Studies at the University of Wisconsin,
Madison. He is the author of Changes in the Land: Indians, Colonists, and the
Ecology of New England and, most recently, Nature's Metropolis: Chicago and
the Great West, which was awarded the Bancroft Prize in American History.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?832374000,rev">Search</a>
