<p><b>Biography</p></b>

JOEL E. COHEN is head of the Laboratory of Populations at Rockefeller
University. His degrees, all from Harvard University, include two doctorates,
one in applied mathematics and the other in population sciences and tropical
public health. A former member of Harvard's Society of Fellows and winner of
a MacArthur Foundation award, he is a prolific author, with publications
ranging over various fields, including demography, ecology, population
genetics, epidemiology, animal behavior, and mathematics; his nonacademic
output includes works of poetry, music, and humor. He lives in New York City
with his wife and their two children.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?832374000,rev">Search</a>
