<h2>D<font size=-1>ISMEMBERING</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> M<font size=-1>ALE</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Joanna Bourke. <br>
<i>Reaktion; 336 pages; &#163;19.95.</i> <i>University of Chicago; $32.50.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="6jb150.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Joanna Bourke is Lecturer in Economic and Social History at Birkbeck
College, University of London. She is the author of Husbandry to Housewifery:
Women, Economic Change and Housework in Ireland, 1890-1914 (1993) and
Working Class Cultures in Britain, 1890-1960 (1994).<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?832374000,rev">Search</a>
