<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Since leaving the Diplomatic Service, Michael Shea was, most prominently,
Press Secretary to Her Majesty the Queen for ten years. He is now chairman of
an international executive search group and a number of other companies, and
is a Visiting Professor at the University of Strathclyde. He has published fifteen
books of fiction and non-fiction, including most recently the highly praised The
Spin Doctor.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?832374000,rev">Search</a>
