<html><head><title>Biography</title></head><body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td><td align=center valign=top><a href="1cl1-1.jpg"><img src="1cs1-1.gif" alt="jacket thumbnail"><p>Full image</a></td></tr></table><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td><h2>TCHAIKOVSKY</h2><p>By Anthony Holden. <i>Bantam; 490 pages; &#163;18.99</i></h2><p><a href="1jb1-1.htm">Jacket copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b><br><p>Anthony Holden's best-selling biographies of Laurence Olivier and Prince Charles have been hailed on both sides of the Atlantic as 'definitive'. Big Deal, his classic account of a year as a professional poker player was praised by enthusiasts ranging from Walter Matthau to Salman Rushdie</p><p></p><p>Holden is also an admired translator of works from the classics to opera, including Greek Pastoral Poetry for Penguin Classics and Don Giovanni and The Barber of Seville for English National Opera.</p><p></p><p>Born in Lancashire and educated at Oxford, Holden enjoyed an award-wining career in journalism before becoming a prolific writer and broadcaster. He is married to the American writer Cindy Blake, and has three small sons.</p><br><a href="http://www.economist.com/review/">Review Index</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/">The Economist</a></td></tr></table></body></html>
