<html><head><title>Biography</title></head><body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td><td align=center valign=top><a href="1cl8-2.jpg"><img src="1cs8-2.gif" alt="jacket thumbnail"><p>Full image</a></td></tr></table><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td><h2>UNITED NATIONS</h2><p>By Stanley Meisler. <i>Atlantic Monthly Press; 288 pages; $24</i></h2><p><a href="1jb8-2.htm">Jacket copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b><br><p>STANLEY MEISLER is a former foreign correspondent for the Los Angeles Times, he covered Nairobi, Mexico City, much of Latin America, Paris, and Madrid. He is now in the Times's Washington Bureau, where he covers foreign affairs and the U.N.</p><p>Stanley Meisler was born in New York and received his BA in English Literature from the City College of New York. He did graduate work in English Literature and African History at the University of at Berkeley, and received a Fellowship from the Ford Foundation in Area Training in African Studies. He worked as a reporter with the Associated Press from 1954 to 1964; was a foreign correspondent for the Los Angeles Times in Nairobi (covering all of the continent except North Africa), from 1967 to 1973; in Mexico City (covering much of Latin America), from 1973 to 1976; in Madrid (covering Spain and Portugal), from 1976 to 1978; in Canada, Nicaragua, France, Belgium, Switzerland, and Spain from 1978 to 1991; and has been a correspondent for the United Nations since 1991. He is the author of the 1992 Praeger award-winning book Africa's Media Image, the recipient of the Society of Professional Journalists Sigma Delta Chi Award, and the 1992 recipient of the Korn-Ferry Award for International Exellence in United Nations Reporting. He has also written numerous articles for, among others, such publications as The Atlantic Monthly Magazine, Foreign Affairs, The Nation, Smithsonian, The Columbla Journalism Review, The Quarterly Journal of Military History, and Foreign Policy.</p><br><a href="http://www.economist.com/review/">Review Index</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/">The Economist</a></td></tr></table></body></html>
