<html><head><title>Biography</title></head><body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td><td align=center valign=top><a href="1cl12-1.jpg"><img src="1cs12-1.gif" alt="jacket thumbnail"><p>Full image</a></td></tr></table><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td><h2>THE OXFORD ILLUSTRATED HISTORY OF THEATRE</h2><p>Edited by John Russell Brown. <i>Oxford University Press; 592 pages; &#163;25; $45</i></h2><p><a href="1jb12-1.htm">Jacket copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b><br><p>John Russell Brown is Professor of Theatre at the University of Michigan and was for fifteen years Associate of the National Theatre in London. His publications include Discovering Shakespeare (1981), Free Shakespeare (1974), Theatre Language (1972), Shakespeare's Plays in Performance (1966), and editions of plays by Shakespeare, Webster, Marlowe, and the 'Wakefield Master' He has directed many plays for both professional and student companies, working in theatres in England, North America, Poland, India, and New Zealand.</p><br><a href="http://www.economist.com/review/">Review Index</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/">The Economist</a></td></tr></table></body></html>
