<hr size=5 width=70 align=left>
<h4>Japanese non-fiction</h4>

<ol>
<li>Matsumoto <i> by Hitoshi Matsumoto</i>. &#160; Japan's favourite comedian</li>
<li>A Great Revolution in the Brain World <i> by Shigeo Haruyama</i>. &#160; Oriental ways of thinking</li>
<li>A Companion for Ageing   <i> by Sadako Sawamura</i>. &#160; An ageing actress's life</li>
<li>Sokagakkai Dracula Theory  <i> by Science of Happiness</i>. &#160; One sect attacks another</li>
<li>The Qualifications of a Champion <i> by Katsuya Nomura</i>. &#160; Reminiscences of a baseball hero</li>
<li>That's the Way it is <i> by Momoko Sakura</i>. &#160; Essays from a popular cartoonist</li>
<li>Sacrifice <i> by Kunio Yanagida</i>. &#160; Eleven days with his brain-dead son</li>
<li>Yumi Tanimura <i> by Akira Kitajima</i>. &#160; Photographs of the musician's tour of Brazil</li>
<li>Declaration of Arrogance <i> by Yoshinori Kobayashi</i>. &#160; A cartoonist's candid opinions</li>
<li>Through Mountains and Rivers <i> by Ryuzo Sejima</i>. &#160; Autobiography of a businessman and ex-war criminal</li>
</ol>
</td></tr></table>

