</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> E<font size=-1>ND</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> N<font size=-1>ATION-</font>S<font size=-1>TATE</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Jean-Marie Guhenno; translated by Victoria Elliott. <br><i>University of Minnesota Press; 160 pages; $19.95</i></p>
<p><a href="2jb13-3.html">Jacket Copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b></p>
<p>Jean-Marie Guehenno is a graduate of the Ecole Normale Superieure and the Ecole Nationale d'Administration. He has taught geopolitics at the Institut d'Etudes Politiques and has contributed to numerous newspapers and magazines, including Le Monde, the International Herald Tribune, Politique Etrangere, and Politique Internationale. The former French Cultural Consul to the United States, he was also the head of the policy planning staff in the French Foreign Ministry from 1989 to 1993 and is currently serving as France's ambassador to the European Union.<p>
<p>Victoria Elliott is a copy editor on the foreign news desk at the San Francisco Chronicle and worked for the International Herald lkEbune and at Newsweek in Paris from 1976 to 1987. She has translated several volumes for the French publisher Gallimard.<p>
<p>
<p>
