<html><head><title>AN IMAGE TO DIE FOR</title></head><body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td><td align=center valign=top>
<a href="2cl1-3.jpg"><img src="2cs1-3.gif" alt="review graphic"><p>Full Image</a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>A<font size=-1>N</font> I<font size=-1>MAGE</font> <font size=-1>TO</font> D<font size=-1>IE</font> F<font size=-1>OR</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Mike Phillips. <br><i>HarperCollins; 240 pages; 14.99.</i></p>
<p><a href="2bt1-3.html">Biography</a></p><p><b>Jacket Copy</b></p>
<p>The brutal murders of young woman, Helen Ross, and her children on a London housing estate seem straightforward to the police - the husband is arrested and convicted. But independent TV producer Wyndham Davis has unearthed crucial evidence which could overturn the conviction.<p>
<p>Black journalist Sam Dean is invited to the housing estate where a mystery witness is being interviewed, but before the interview is over, one of the programme's researchers is viciously stabbed to death. Sickened by the incident, Sam isn't wild about the job Wyndham's offering - that of tracking down Helen Ross's lover - but emotional pressure is brought to bear from an unexpected quarter.<p>
<p>As he embarks on his search for the missing man, Sam realizes that there is more than one agenda here. There ore secrets from Wyndhum's own life influencing events and Sam is getting sucked right into the heart of the mystery, with potentially lethal consequences. Tough, vivid, shocking An Image to Die For is a stunning new novel from one of today's foremost crime writers.<p>
<p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?819064800,rev">Search</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
