</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>A<font size=-1>N</font> I<font size=-1>MAGE</font> <font size=-1>TO</font> D<font size=-1>IE</font> F<font size=-1>OR</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Mike Phillips. <br><i>HarperCollins; 240 pages; 14.99.</i></p>
<p><a href="2jb1-3.html">Jacket Copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b></p>
<p>Mike Phillips is a Londoner and author of several books and screenplays as well as his series of Sam Dean novels, published to universal acclaim. The first, Blood Rights, was serialized for BBC TV; the second, The Late Candidate, won the Crime Writers' Association's Silver Dagger Award. An Image to Die For is his fourth Sam Dean novel.<p>
<p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?819064800,rev">Search</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
