<h2>S<font size=-1>MOKE</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Donald E. Westlake. <br><i>Mysterious Press; 454 pages $21.95</i></p>
<p><a href="2jb1-8.html">Jacket Copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b></p>
<p>DONALD E. WESTLAKE doesn't have his own Washington lobby, but he does have millions of addicted fans. The author of over seventy novels under his own name and a few others, he has written works ranging from high comedy to high crime, from the classic caper The Hot Rock to his most recent, the country-and-western tinged Baby, Would I Lie? His screenplay for the film The Grifters was nominated for an Academy Award, and in 1993 he was named Grand Master by the Mystery Writers of America, a breath-taking honor. He lives in the nonsmoking section of upstate New York with his wife, the writer Abby Adams.<p>
<p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?819064800,rev">Search</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
