<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>W<font size=-1>AYS</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> D<font size=-1>YING</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Zakes Mda. <br><i>Oxford University Press Southern Africa; 199 pages; 35.99 rand.</i></p>
<p><a href="2bt2-2.html">Biography</a></p><p><b>Jacket Copy</b></p>
<p>WAYS OF DYING tells the story of the eccentric but dignified professional mourner, Toloki. His odyssey takes him from a rural village community ot the shabby, vibrant outskirts of a contemporary South African city, where the tenderness that springs up between him and the beautiful and tragic Noria helps them to heal the past. By turns magical, brutal, and funny, this compelling work is a major new contribution to South African writing.<p>
<p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?819064800,rev">Search</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
