<html><head><title>BALKAN ODYSSEY</title></head><body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td><td align=center valign=top>
<a href="2cl7-1.jpg"><img src="2cs7-1.gif" alt="review graphic"><p>Full Image</a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0><tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>B<font size=-1>ALKAN</font> O<font size=-1>DYSSEY</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By David Owen. <br><i>Victor Gollancz</i>;<i> 4</i>16<i> pages</i>; <i>20</i>. <font size=-1>CD</font>-<font size=-1>ROM</font><i>. the electric company; standard 25 and academic 150</i></p>
<p><a href="2jb7-1.html">Jacket Copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b></p>
<p>DAVID OWEN was born in Plymouth in 1938 and represented the city in Parliament from 1966 to 1992, when he retired as its longest-serving MP and became Lord Owen of the City of Plymouth. He was Navy Minister from 1968 to 1970, Health Minister from 1974 to 1976 and Foreign Secretary from February 1977 until the General Election of May 1979. A founder of the Social Democratic Party in 1981, he led the party from 1983 to 1987 and from 1988 to 1990. His autobiography, Time to Declare, was published in September 1991. Lord Owen was appointed Co-Chairman of the Steering Committee of the International Conference on the Former Yugoslavia in August 1992 and stepped down in June 1995. He was made a Companion of Honour in 1994.<p>
<p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?819064800,rev">Search</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a> &nbsp; -  &nbsp  <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
</td></tr></table></body></html>
