<h2>F<font size=-1>IDELITY'S</font> W<font size=-1>ORLD</font><br>
</h2>
<p>By Diana Henriques. <br><i>Charles Scribner's Sons; 416 pages; $26</i></p>
<p><a href="2jb12-1.html">Jacket Copy</a></p><p><b>Biography</b></p>
<p>DIANA B. HENRIQUES is an investigative business reporter for The New York Times. She has been nominated for the Pulitzer Prize three times. From 1989 to 1991, her weekly column, "Wall Street," in the Sunday New York Times Business Section, was required reading in financial circles. She was formerly a feature reporter for Barron's. She lives in Hoboken, New Jersey.<p>
<p>
