<h2>F<font size=-1>INAL</font> D<font size=-1>AYS</font>:<br> T<font size=-1>HE</font> I<font size=-1>NSIDE</font> S<font size=-1>TORY</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> <font size=-1>THE C</font><font size=-1>OLLAPSE</font> <font size=-1>OF</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> S<font size=-1>OVIET</font> U<font size=-1>NION</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Andrei Grachev. <br>
<i>Westview Press; 240 pages; $29.50 and &#163;21.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="5jb65.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Andrei Grachev was a foreign policy adviser to Mikhail Gorbachev from 1985
until the autumn of 1991, when he became press secretary. He is currently a
Moscow News columnist and a senior research fellow at the Institute of World
Economy and International Relations in Moscow.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
