<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> L<font size=-1>AST</font> H<font size=-1>UNDRED </font>D<font size=-1>AYS OF THE </font>S<font size=-1>OVIET</font> U<font size=-1>NION</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Boris Pankin. <br>
<i>I.B. Tauris; 288 pages; &#163;19.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="5jb64.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Boris Pankin, Soviet Foreign Minister from the end of August to the end of
November 1991, became Russian Ambassador to London after the Soviet
Collapse. Having left the Russian diplomatic service, he now devotes his time
to writing and political commentary.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
