<h2>T<font size=-1>HEY</font> O<font size=-1>NLY</font> L<font size=-1>OOK</font> D<font size=-1>EAD</font>:<br> W<font size=-1>HY</font> P<font size=-1>ROGRESSIVES</font> W<font size=-1>ILL</font> D<font size=-1>OMINATE</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> N<font size=-1>EXT</font> P<font size=-1>OLITICAL</font> E<font size=-1>RA</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By E. J. Dionne Jr. <br>
<i>Simon &amp; Schuster; 352 pages; $24.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="5jb115.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

E. J. DIONNE JR. is a columnist for The Washington Post. His first book, Why
Americans Hate Politics--a National Book Award nominee, the winner of the
Los Angeles Times Book Prize, and a New York Times Notable Book of the
Year--has already been described as "a classic in American political history."
Dionne lives in Washington, D.C.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
