<html><head><title>U.S.A. 2012</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl107.jpg"><img src="cs107.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>U.S.A. 2012:<br> A<font size=-1>FTER</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> M<font size=-1>IDDLE-CLASS</font> R<font size=-1>EVOLUTION</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Kenneth Dolbeare and Janette Kay Hubbell. <br>
<i>Chatham House; 208 pages; &#163;20 and $25</i>.<br>
</p><br>
<a href="5jb107.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

KEN DOLBEARE and JANETTE HUBBELL, a husband and wife writing
team, are both former teachers who now run their own business. Recognizing
but refusing to accept the discouraging future that currently looms for their six
young adult children (ranging in age from 17 to 34), they set about to explore
ways that a bright and hopeful future might be constructed in the United States
by motivated middleclass Americans.
<p>Just as important, they sought to find a means of communicating the sense of purpose, hope, and self-confidence that are vital to sustained and effective political action. The result is a brief and readable book combining fictional interviews from 2012 and solid, data-based analysis and prescription. The intended audience is all who care about the American future, whether politically right or left or middle, and whether young or old or middle-aged.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/archive.html">Review Archive</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/review/index.html">Review List</a>
 &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="review.html">This Review</a></p>
</td></tr></table></body></html>
