Japan at the age of sixteen. He read Asian Studies at Harvard University in the
early 1970s and subsequently attended the Harvard Business School. Since then
he has been an investment banker in Tokyo with Chase Manhattan and
Goldman Sachs, and is now a writer and independent consultant in Tokyo. His
articles and columns have appeared in the Harvard Business Review and the
New York Times.<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
