</p><br>
<a href="5jb122.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

James Elkins is an art historian at the School of the Art Institute in Chicago. He
has written on images in Western and non-Western art and in science,
medicine, mathematics, computer graphics, and archaeology. He has two books
forthcoming: Our Beautiful, Dry, and Distant Texts, about the ways that art
historians write, and Pictures, and the Words That Fail Them, concerning the
difficulty of describing images. He spent his childhood in Ithaca, New York, a
half-mile through the woods from Cornell University, and he now lives in
