<a href="5jb123.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

Bryan Magee is a noted philosopher and broadcaster; his publications include
Men of Ideas (1982) and The Great Philosophers (1988). He has held visiting
Fellowships at Yale and Oxford Universities among others; he has been
Honorary Senior Research Fellow in History of Ideas, King's College London,
since 1984; he is an Honorary Fellow of Keble College, Oxford.
<p>The late Martin Milligan was Head of Philosophy at the University of Leeds until shortly before his recent death; he had been there since 1959. He was a well-known blind activist, campaigning for the equal treatment of and integration into sighted society of blind people.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
