<h2>S<font size=-1>TEPS</font> F<font size=-1>ROM</font> P<font size=-1>ARADISE</font>.<br></h2>
<p> By Timeri Murari. <br>
<i>Hodder &amp; Stoughton; 487 pages; &#163;16.99.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="5jb109.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>

TIMERI N. MURARI was born in Madras. He studied, travelled and worked as
a journalist in the United States, Canada and England before returning there to
live.
<p>His highly acclaimed novels include Field of Honour, Lovers Are Not People, The Shooter and three historical novels set in India: Taj, The Imperial Agent and The Last Victory.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?829954800,rev">Search</a>
