<IMG SRC="../../econlogosmall.gif" ALIGN="left"><b><H3>&#160; A survey of Britain's new politics </H3></B>

<P>
September 21st 1996<HR>

<H3><A HREF="brit1.html"> All Tories now </A></H3>
<P>
<i> Labour and the Tories have much in common these days. For one thing, neither party offers Britain the ideas it needs </i>

<H3><A HREF="brit2.html"> The state we're really in </A></H3>
<P>
<I> The past 17 years have done the British economy a power of good </I> 

<H3><A HREF="brit3.html"> The Thatcher revolution </A></H3>
<P>
<I> The Tories' greatest achievements were to crush the unions and sell the nationalised industries</I>

<H3><A HREF="brit4.html"> The outsiders </A></H3>
<p>
<I> Surging unemployment has been the Tories' greatest failure. What can be done about it? </I>

<H3><A HREF="brit5.html"> Cradle to grave </A> </H3>
<P>
<I> What should become of the welfare state? </I>

<H3><A HREF="brit6.html"> Power and the people </A></H3>
<P>
<I> The most contentious issues for the next government will be constitutional ones </I> 

<H3><A HREF="brit7.html"> The reluctant European </A></H3>
<P>
<I> No less than its partners, Britain needs a clearer view of what the European Union is for </I>

<H3><A HREF="brit8.html"> An <i>Economist</i> manifesto</A></H3>
<P>
<I> A few ideas </I>
<p>
