<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>A survey of international banking</TITLE><BODY><BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><H1>The domino effect</H1><P><IMG SRC="ibcov.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <H3>A survey of international banking</H3><P>April 27th, 1996<HR><H3><A HREF="ibsu1.html">Coping with the ups and downs</A></H3><P><I>Fears about systemic risk in banking have led to calls for ever more rules and regulations. But, asks MartinGiles, would they be part of the solution or part of the problem? </I><H3><A HREF="ibsu2.html">System failure</A></H3><P><I>Collapse is less likely than it used to be, but the possibility is no less frightening </I> <H3><A HREF="ibsu3.html">Dangerous deriving?</A></H3><H3><A HREF="ibsu4.html">Can't pay, won't pay</A></H3><P><I>Watch out for blockages in the financial plumbing</I> <H3><A HREF="ibsu5.html">A financial horror story</A> </H3><P><I>How safety nets create banking zombies</I> <H3><A HREF="ibsu6.html">Trouble in Tokyo</A> </H3><P><I>Moral hazard has played a part in Japan's banking disaster, too</I> <H3><A HREF="ibsu7.html">Safe banking</A></H3><P><I>Like safe sex, safe banking requires effective precautions </I> <H3><A HREF="ibsu8.html">A novel bank statement</A></H3><P><H3><A HREF="ibsu9.html">Private ideas for public policy</A></H3><P><I>A different insurance policy would produce a very different type of bank</I><H3><A HREF="ibsu10.html">A standard dose</A></H3><P><I>Cross-border prescriptions for banking systems can sometimes do more harm than good </I><H3><A HREF="ibsu11.html">Extinguishing banking's fires</A></H3><P><I>Bad banks are usually the product of bad macroeconomic policy</I><P><P><H3><A HREF="ibsu12.html">Bibliography</A></H3><P><HR><H3><left>Comments on this survey?</left></H3><p>Please send letters to be considered for publication to <A HREF="mailto:letters@economist.com">letters@economist.com</A>.<br><p align=left><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Pag