<p><font size=+1><b><a href="http://www.economist.com/review/rev4/rv1/review.html">Go directly to jail</a></b></font><br>
<font size=-1>The Oxford History of Prisons: The Practice of Punishment in Western Society&nbsp; <i>Edited by Norval Morris and David Rothman.</i>
 -- Western European Penal Systems&nbsp; <i>Edited by Vincenzo Ruggiero, Mick Ryan and Joe Sim.</i>
 -- A Reader on Punishment&nbsp; <i>Edited by Antony Duff and David Garland.</i>
 -- Punishment: A Philosophy and Public Affairs Reader&nbsp; <i>Edited by John Simmons, Marshall Cohen, Joshua Cohen and Charles Beitz.</i>
 -- Guilty&nbsp; <i>By Harold Rothwax.</i>
 -- In the Name of the Law&nbsp; <i>By David Rose.</i>
