<h2></i>V<font size=-1>ANISHING</font> D<font size=-1>IASPORA</font><br></h2>
<p>By Bernard Wasserstein.<br>
<i>Hamish Hamilton; 352 pages; &#163;20. Harvard; $27.95</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb26.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>Bernard Wasserstein was born in London in 1948 and educated at Balliol and Nuffield Colleges, Oxford. Since 1982 he has been Professor of History at Brandeis University in Massachusetts. His earlier books include Britain and the Jews of Europe 1939-1945, The British in Palestine and The Secret Lives of Trebitsch Lincoln, which received the Golden Dagger Award for non-fiction in 1988. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
