<h2></i>US I<font size=-1>NTELLIGENCE</font> <font size=-1>AT</font> <font size=-1>THE</font> C<font size=-1>ROSSROADS</font><br></h2>
<p>Edited by Roy Godson, Ernest May and Gary Schmitt.<br>
<i>Brassey's; 315 pages; $25.95 and &#163;20.95.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb35.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p><p>The Editors</p>
</p><p>ROY GODSON is a professor of government at Georgetown University and coordinator of the Consortium for the Study of Intelligence. ERNEST R. MAY is Charles Warren Professor of History at Harvard University and co-chair of the Working Group on Intelligence Reform. GARY SCHMITT is a senior fellow at the National Strategy Information Center and former staff director of the President's Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board. <br>
</p>
