<h2></i>T<font size=-1>WILIGHT</font> W<font size=-1>ARRIORS</font><br></h2>
<p>By Martin Arostegui.<br>
<i>Bloomsbury; 313 pages; &#163;16.99</i>.<br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb53.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>MARTIN C. AROSTEGUI is a writer and freelance journalist who specializes in terrorism, military and political affairs. He covered the Gulf War in 1990-91 and has reported from other troublespots around the world. His articles have appeared in many newspapers and magazines, including the Economist, Sunday Telegraph, the European, the Australian and Combat and Survival. He worked for several years as a specialist consultant with Risks International, a counter- terrorism think tank in Washington D.C. He is the author of a novel, The Bent Hostage. He was born in Manila in 1955, and now lives in Spain. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
