<h2>D<font size=-1>UMBING</font> D<font size=-1>OWN</font> O<font size=-1>UR</font> K<font size=-1>IDS</font><br></h2>
<p>By Charles Sykes.<br>
<i>St Martin's; 341 pages; $23.95.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb33.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>CHARLES J. SYKES  is the author of three previous books, ProfScam, The Hollow Men, and A Nation of Victims. A journalist who specializes in education issues, he has written for and is frequently quoted by newspapers around the nation, including The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal, USA Today, The Los Angeles Times, and the Chicago Tribune. He has lectured at universities and before parents' groups about the subject of schooling. A senior fellow at the Wisconsin Policy Research Institute, Sykes lives with his wife and three children in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
