http://www.economist.com:80/review/rev3/rv3/3bt34.html 199.173.162.110 19970114030104 text/html 1948
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.12
Date: Tuesday, 14-Jan-97 02:56:55 GMT
Last-modified: Thursday, 08-Aug-96 14:04:05 GMT
Content-length: 1762
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<html><head><title>The Manufactured Crisis</title></head>
<body background="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rback.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width=100% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td valign=top align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/rlogo.gif" alt="review logo"></td>
<td align=center valign=top>
<a href="cl34.jpg"><img src="cs34.gif" alt="cover image"><p>Full Image</p></a>
</td></tr></table>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0>
<tr><td valign=bottom align=left><img src="http://www.economist.com/review/images/instrap.gif"></td><td>
<h2>T<font size=-1>HE</font> M<font size=-1>ANUFACTURED</font> C<font size=-1>RISIS</font><br></h2>
<p>By David Berliner and Bruce Biddle.<br>
<i>Addison-Wesley; 414 pages; $25.</i><br>
</p><br>
<a href="3jb34.html">Jacket Copy</a><br>
<p><b>Biography</p></b>
<p>
</p><p>
</p><p>David C. Berliner is the 1994 recipient of the NEA's highest honor, its Friends of Education Award. He is Professor of both Psychology and Education and Curriculum and Instruction at Arizona State University in Tempe.
</p><p>Bruce J. Biddle is Editor of the journal Social Psychology of Education, and is Professor of both Psychology and Sociology and Director of the Center for Research in Social Behavior at the University of Missouri. <br>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.economist.com/index.html"><i>The Economist</i> Home Page</a> &nbsp; - &nbsp; <a href="http://www.economist.com/cgi-bin/search_form.cgi?824508000,rev">Search</a>
